data.title: Good Mexican food - not upscale but authentic
data.text: I think if you set your expectations realistically, this is a good Mexican restaurant.  No the atmosphere is not the greatest, the carpet is a bit worn, but the food and the Margharita I ordered, top shelf, was excellent.  This place is inexpensive and family friendly... Families with children running around.  Did not bother me at all.  If I was going on a date and wanted quiet ambience, I would have wanted something better but also likely more expensive.  You get what you pay for.

data.title: NASTY!!!!!
data.text: Do not go here, this place is nasty.  Bathrooms were disgusting and the carpet is stained and pulling up.  The service was slow despite no one bing in the place.  The food was tasteless and nasty.  Ordered a combo with a beef enchilada and a tostada.  Both had no flavor; this place makes Taco Bell look GREAT!!!!  The bug that crawled across the table was an extra treat.  Service was slow and inattentive; I had to go to the register to get a bill.  I cannot emphasize enough:  DO NOT EAT HERE!!!!!  Second word meal I have had at a restaurant.

data.title: Honest recipes with true Mexican taste
data.text: Los Cabos has been open for a few years now and every year the food gets better.  The ingredients are always fresh, the preparation simple and the flavor clean and rich.  If you go in for a $6.50 lunch of Pollo con Crema or the luncheon fajitas, you will be greeted quickly, served quickly and allowed to linger over your meal.  In the evening, as the place fills up, there's always room for one more and the service is just as attentive and cheerful as at noon.  The menu presents the usual Mexican restaurant choices, but the quality is exceptional.  The food is simply prepared without additives that often make restaurant food a gamble.  In fact, the Los Cabos chicken soup has become our go-to take out when someone in the house has a bad cold or the flu.

data.title: Good quality Mexican food
data.text: The food in Los cabos is extremely good and genuine mexican food. The service is also good as well. (although one waitress doesn't have much english I generally don't mind this in a Mexican restaurant) in particular the sweet tea in Los cabos is the best I had in any restaurant (so I strongly recommend drinking tea there) I ordered the speed gonzalez, taco primo and flan all of which were delicious. All in all this is a great Mexican restaurant 5 stars.

data.title: Los Cabos great food
data.text: Great service very friendly.  Fresh and tasty food. Conveniently located Walton Way hospital area! Good menu selection

data.title: Hit or miss
data.text:
This place can be very good, or not.  Seems to depend on who's working and how well they speak English.  We order carry out fairly often and have learned to check our orders before leaving.  That being said, when this restaurant is on its game, the food is delicious!
I recommend the fish tacos with pineapple salsa on flour tortillas.  The corn is good if ordered to eat in, but by the time they get back to the office, the corn tortillas have disintegrated.
